Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle at neck join to sharpish turn. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Clay fine pink-buff.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Name Damophilos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0340.06.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1031)
